tables and its tags and its attributes

<table></table>--> used to create a table
<thead></thead>--> used to create a table header
<tbody></tbody>--> used to create a table body
<tfoot></tfoot>--> used to create a table footer

<tr></tr>--> used to create a row in the table
<td></td>--> used to create a cell in the table
<th></th>--> used to create a header cell in the table

rowspan: specifies the number of rows a cell should span
colspan: specifies the number of columns a cell should span

cellpadding: specifies the space between the cell content and its border
cellspacing: specifies the space between cells in a table
align: specifies the alignment of the content in a cell (left, right, center)
width: specifies the width of the table or a cell
height: specifies the height of the table or a cell

<!-- Pseudo classes and pseudo elements -->
<!-- Pseudo classes and pseudo elements are used in CSS to apply styles based on the state of an element or its position in the document. -->
<!-- Pseudo classes are used to style an element based on its state, such as when it is hovered over or focused. Pseudo elements are used to style a specific part of an element, such as the first letter or line of a paragraph. -->

pseudo element and pseudo class

pseudo element:
::first-letter
::first-line
::selection
::before
::after
::marker


pseudo class:
:focus
:hover
:active
:visited
:link

anchor tag and its attributes:
href: specifies the URL of the page the link goes to
target: specifies where to open the linked document
rel: specifies the relationship between the current document and the linked document



